I remember reading a bizarre parabiblical myth about an Old Testament figure's brother, can't remember the name. God decided to punish all in that man's village by turning the water into subtle poison, that made everyone mad. But he took pity on the man and told him his plan

The next day the man everyone drinking water and going mad, but he knew the reason, so he went away from the village, in the forest, and drank from the river there. He got so lonely he could no longer bear it. Meanwhile everyone in the village continued living as madmen

Finally he realized his life now was worse than that of the mindless villagers, so he went to the village well and drank from it. He lost his mind and lived happily with the others, all of them mad, but none of them able to understand it. Bliss.
